headline.main: Abroad; The Merger of Two Big Threes Into One Big Four

lead_paragraph: On the basis of a Reuter dispatch from Lisbon, stating that the Big Three of the Eastern war have concluded a meeting in Cairo and have proceeded to Iran for a meeting of the Big Three of the Western war, it appears that the "diplomatic block-buster" the world has been waiting for is not one conference but two.
abstract: A O McCormick comment on Cairo-Iran confs
